216
00:09:16,370 --> 00:09:19,839
It wasn’t until 1971 that the UN

217
00:09:19,839 --> 00:09:22,310
switched to the People’s Republic of China,

218
00:09:22,310 --> 00:09:25,029
which is run by the Chinese Communist Party.

219
00:09:25,029 --> 00:09:27,480
The US made the switch in 1979,

220
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:30,670
and 90% of other countries have followed suit.

221
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:32,320
The Chinese Communist Party has basically

222
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,150
made the entire world pick:

223
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:37,300
“You can only recognize one China,

224
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:38,769
so will it be us,

225
00:09:38,769 --> 00:09:41,110
the big China with a billion people?

226
00:09:41,110 --> 00:09:44,310
Or will it be the puny island of Taiwan?”

227
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:48,079
But I believe that’s a false choice.

228
00:09:48,079 --> 00:09:49,550
More and more, in Taiwan,

229
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:52,780
the people see themselves as a completely
separate nation,

230
00:09:52,780 --> 00:09:54,360
an already independent country

231
00:09:54,360 --> 00:09:57,230
with their own identity that should be recognized

232
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:59,210
by the international community.

233
00:09:59,210 --> 00:10:01,040
It’s just that other countries

234
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:03,170
have all agreed to the false choice,

235
00:10:03,170 --> 00:10:05,850
that there can only be one China.

236
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:07,880
So they’ve all picked only one China

237
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:10,079
to have diplomatic relations with.

238
00:10:10,079 --> 00:10:13,180
In theory, the United States could officially
recognize

239
00:10:13,180 --> 00:10:17,540
both the PRC and Taiwan as individual countries.

240
00:10:17,540 --> 00:10:18,750
And if they did that,

241
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:21,740
then other countries would probably do that
too.

242
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:25,560
But that would be a dramatic change in US
foreign policy,

243
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:27,340
and it would anger the Communist Party

244
00:10:27,340 --> 00:10:30,240
to an extraordinary degree.

245
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:32,180
The alternative is to continue pretending

246
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:34,930
that Taiwan isn’t really a country,

247
00:10:34,930 --> 00:10:36,320
but that’s also...

248
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:38,269
not a great long-term solution,

249
00:10:38,269 --> 00:10:39,980
since it means constantly pretending

250
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:42,080
something isn’t the way it really is.

251
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,660
I don’t have the answer here.

252
00:10:44,660 --> 00:10:47,380
But there’s another possible scenario, too.

253
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:50,450
If the Chinese Communist Party collapses someday,

254
00:10:50,450 --> 00:10:51,889
there might be a new government

255
00:10:51,889 --> 00:10:53,930
that doesn’t care so much about claiming

256
00:10:53,930 --> 00:10:56,690
Taiwan as a province of China.

257
00:10:56,690 --> 00:10:59,170
And then the situation would resolve itself.

258
00:10:59,170 --> 00:11:02,759
Wait...if the Chinese Communist Party collapses,

259
00:11:02,759 --> 00:11:06,210
then what would I be uncensoring on this show?

260
00:11:06,210 --> 00:11:08,820
I’d be out of a job!

261
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:11,480
I guess there’s always Russia Uncensored.

